UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. YIJUN ZHOU, Defendant-Appellant. No. 14-50288 United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. August 17, 2016

D.C. No. 2:13-cr-00766-PSG-l

Jean-Claude Andre, Assistant U.S. Attorney, Ronald L. Cheng, O’Melveny & Myers LLP, Office of the U.S. Attorney, Los Angeles, CA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Jonathan D. Libby, Esq., FPDCA— Federal Public Defender’s Office, Los An-geles, CA, for Defendant-Appellant. *1014Before: TASHIMA, SILVERMAN, and GRABER, Circuit Judges.

ORDER

The opinion and dissent filed on August 10, 2016, and published at —- F.3d-, 2016. WL 4205942, are withdrawn. The opinion shall not be cited as precedent by or to any court of the Ninth Circuit. The court will file a new opinion in due course.
